column31: 1/ 15 - What are you like? Rugged - Delicate.Rugged: strong & powerful. Delicate: being vulnerable.
column32: 2/ 15 - What are you like? Exitable - Calm.Exitable: readily roused into action / responsive to stimulation. Calm: inner peace / absence of strong emotions.
column33: 3/ 15 - What are you like? Uncomfortable - Comfortable.Uncomfortable: causing discomfort or annoyance / feeling uneasy. Comfortable: affording or enjoying physical contentment and security / free from doubt, free from stress or tension.
column34: 4/ 15 - What are you like? Dominating - Submissive.Dominating: being in control / have power or influence over. Submissive: ready to conform to the authority or will of others.
column35: 5/ 15 - What are you like? Thrifty - Indulgent.Thrifty: using money and other resources carefully and not wastefully. Indulgent: the attitude of allowing yourself or someone else to have something enjoyable, or the act of having something enjoyable (easily giving in).
column36: 6/ 15 - What are you like? Pleasant - Unpleasant.Pleasant: polite or agreeable. Unpleasant: harsh, offensive, disagreeable.
column37: 7/ 15 - What are you like? Contemporary - Non contemporary.Contemporary: modern / present-day. Non contemporary: old-fashioned.
column38: 8/ 15 - What are you like? Organized - Unorganized.Organized: give an orderly structure to /  systematize. Unorganized: not orderly / destroy the system or order; throw into confusion.
column39: 9/ 15 - What are you like? Rational - Emotional.Rational: cool / task- and logic-focused / pragmatic. Emotional: feelings-focused / intense / impulsive.
column40: 10/ 15 - What are you like? Youthful - Mature.Youthful: having the vitality or freshness of youth. Mature: fully developed / grown up in terms of physical appearance, behaviour or thinking.
column41: 11/ 15 -  What are you like? Formal / Informal.Formal: being in accord with established forms, conventions and requirements. Informal: relaxed and friendly /  not following strict rules of how to behave or do something.
column42: 12/ 15 - What are you like? Orthodox - Liberal.Orthodox: conforming to the established, accepted or traditional doctrines. Liberal: openness / more tolerance for change.
column43: 13/ 15 - What are you like? Complex - Simple.Complex: someone who is harder to gauge in terms of opinions, interests, experiences, abilities and knowledge than average. Simple: showing little deviation from the norm within their social class, sex, sexuality, age, appearance, geographical place of origin, political affiliation and so on.
column44: 14/ 15 - What are you like? Colorless - Colorful.Colorless: preferation of the ordinary. Colorful: controversial and colorful character.
column45: 15/ 15 - What are you like? Modest - Vain.Modest: Not bragging or boasting about oneself or one's achievements / humble. Vain: Excessive pride in or admiration of one's own abilities, appearance or achievements.
